                            <comment id="109734" author="olivergierke" created="Sun, 16 Nov 2014 23:28:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Boot 1.2.0.M2 was still on the 2.2.0 (Evans GA) version of Spring Data REST which unfortunately included &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAREST-381&quot; title=&quot;Controllers for Alps and repository listing get listed under the root even if a base URI is configured&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DATAREST-381&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DATAREST-381&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. This has been fixed with Evans SR1 (Spring Data REST 2.2.1) and is already picked up by Spring Boot 1.1.9 and 1.2.0 RC1. Upgrading to those should let you see the bug fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
